{{no footnotes|date=January 2013}} {{Infobox person |image = |imagesize = | name = Antônio Carlos Bernardes Gomes (Mussum) | birth_date = April 7, 1941 | birth_place = [[Rio de Janeiro (city)|Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]] | death_date = July 29, 1994 (aged 53) | death_place = [[São Paulo (city)|São Paulo]], [[Brazil]] | othername = | occupation = [[Actor]], [[musician]] | yearsactive = }}
'''Antônio Carlos Bernardes Gomes''' (April 7, 1941 in [[Rio de Janeiro (city)|Rio de Janeiro]] – July 29, 1994 in [[São Paulo (city)|São Paulo]]), known artistically as '''Mussum''' ({{IPA-pt|muˈsũ}})) was a famous [[Brazil]]ian [[actor]] and [[musician]], notable for being a member of the comedic group [[Os Trapalhões]]. He was also member of the musical group Os Originais do Samba (The Originals of Samba).
He died due to complications after a [[heart]] [[Organ transplantation|transplant]] in 1994.
==Television== *Bairro Feliz (TV Globo, 1965) *Os Trapalhões (TV Excelsior, 1969) *Os Trapalhões (TV Tupi, 1974—1976) *Os Trapalhões (TV Globo, 1977—1993) *Criança Esperança (TV Globo, 1986–1993)
